
# Java Programming Practice Repository

Welcome to my **Java Programming Repository** 🎉
This repository contains all the **examples, exercises, and mini-projects** I’ve completed while learning Java from the **BroCode YouTube Channel**.

The purpose of this repo is to **practice Java fundamentals, Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), and problem-solving**, while building a collection of reusable code and projects.

---

## 📚 Topics Covered

* **Basics**: Variables, Data Types, Input/Output, Operators
* **Control Structures**: If-Else, Switch, Loops (for, while, do-while)
* **Methods**: Parameters, Return values, Overloading
* **Arrays & Strings**: 1D/2D Arrays, String operations, StringBuilder
* **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)**

  * Classes & Objects
  * Constructors
  * Inheritance
  * Polymorphism
  * Encapsulation
  * Abstraction
* **Exception Handling**
* **Collections Framework**: ArrayList, HashMap, HashSet, etc.
* **File Handling**
* **Mini Projects** (tutorial-based + personal practice)

---

## 🚀 Mini Projects

A few projects included in this repository:

* Calculator
* Tic-Tac-Toe Game
* Banking System Simulation
* Student Management System
* Simple GUI Programs (Swing / JavaFX basics)

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies

* **Language**: Java
* **IDE**: VS Code / IntelliJ IDEA
* **Version Control**: Git & GitHub

---

## 📌 How to Run

1. Download or clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/java-programming.git
   ```
2. Open the file in **VS Code** or any Java-supported IDE.
3. Compile and run with:

   ```bash
   javac FileName.java
   java FileName
   ```

